Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.08,0:00:04.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.92,0:00:08.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bring you miraculous illusions that \Nmake this town sparkle at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.21,0:00:12.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What is the final destination \Nof this jewel with a past?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.49,0:00:21.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now, how should I serve up \Nthose three crows?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.52,0:00:24.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.13,0:00:32.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A flying figure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.35,0:00:33.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-That's right, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.88,0:00:38.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's a black silhouette holding on\N to a paraglider next to Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.88,0:00:39.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.28,0:00:41.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On the back of the paraglider...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.13,0:00:44.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A... a cat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.54,0:00:47.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My name is Chat Noir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.36,0:00:49.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sunday at 9:00 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.18,0:00:53.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to our showdown \Nat Hotel Ocean at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.73,0:00:57.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right. You capture Chat Noir,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.90,0:01:01.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and you can take back the \Nsix cat's-eyes he stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.88,0:01:04.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's the point of this whole exhibit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.30,0:01:11.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you don't take Chat Noir seriously, \Nyou're in for serious trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.90,0:01:15.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Aoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.92,0:01:19.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can't afford to lose this contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.96,0:01:24.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You will be wearing the Golden Eye\N on your finger
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.08,0:01:27.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and waiting with it on top of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.23,0:01:36.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-What is this weird line of sight?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.19,0:02:04.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So, how are you going to attack, \NKid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.16,0:02:12.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm already set.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.00,0:03:46.99,Signs - Thief Title,,0,0,11,,{\fad(0,500)}Golden Eye (Part Two):\NKid Versus Chat Noir: Endgame
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.83,0:03:51.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, it's 8:55p.m.. Five minutes before \Nthe theft is scheduled to be committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.49,0:03:54.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Central security room.\N What's the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Right! Everything is going \Naccording to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.01,0:04:00.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Elevators 1, 2, 3, and 4
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.49,0:04:03.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,are stopped at the top, the 30th, floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:06.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The elevator controls are locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.71,0:04:11.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All stairways from the top floor to \Nthe roof and from the top floor down
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:13.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,have been sealed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:15.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:18.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maintain that status until \NI order you otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.85,0:04:21.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's perfect, Cartier-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.79,0:04:27.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now just protect that ring, \Nthe Mitsuishi family treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.04,0:04:30.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,from Chat Noir and\N Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.55,0:04:32.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That ring that \NInspector Nakamori is wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:35.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That memento from Marie Antoinette...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.70,0:04:38.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...the Golden Eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.76,0:04:41.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.06,0:04:44.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't see any helicopters outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.17,0:04:48.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I told you, Investigating Agent Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.43,0:04:55.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As long as we have this glass with \Nembedded titanium alloy wires,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.07,0:05:01.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,no one can use it to get into\N or escape out of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:03.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Helicopters would just be a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.33,0:05:09.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now, given the two thieves in question, \Nthey're likely already impersonating someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:13.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,boldly coming up to this floor, \Neven lurking among us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:20.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.85,0:05:22.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Floodlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:26.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This exhibit is dimly-lit, so we were told \Nto put a spotlight on Inspector Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.44,0:05:32.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, and who gave that order?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.19,0:05:35.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-The inspector! Inspector Nakamori \Nradioed it in a couple minutes ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:40.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, I didn't order that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.70,0:05:42.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-There's no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:45.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Light him up! Turn 'em all on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:48.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Roger! Lighting up banks 1 to 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.49,0:05:52.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Was it really the inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.99,0:05:55.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes! It was definitely his voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.72,0:06:00.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Lighting up banks 6 to 10!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.85,0:06:05.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Lighting up banks 11 to 20!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.82,0:06:11.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-Idiots! If you put them \Non me all at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.86,0:06:13.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:17.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.66,0:06:21.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:23.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A breaker just tripped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:28.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,With this electrical system, the lights \Nwill be back on in ten seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.62,0:06:30.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,More importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:32.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I would like to welcome our guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:39.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The poor thieves who willingly \Nentered this inescapable cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.63,0:06:42.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So, Monsieur Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:46.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Please put on the gas mask \Nand prepare for their attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.64,0:06:49.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:54.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Make sure you keep that fist \Nwith the ring on it closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:06:58.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.98,0:07:02.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...how am I supposed to prepare \Nwhen I can barely see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.02,0:07:08.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.43,0:07:13.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,K-Kid the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:16.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's Kid! Kid's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.34,0:07:18.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,P-Protect the inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.59,0:07:22.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Idiots! Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.22,0:07:23.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's got some cheek, showing up like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:25.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.35,0:07:27.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's my face!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.22,0:07:29.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I've got Kid's leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.47,0:07:32.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's {\i1}my{\i0} leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.36,0:07:36.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting, Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.07,0:07:38.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Waiting for this opportunity!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.11,0:07:44.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Power's coming back on-line!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.11,0:07:45.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Restoring lights to the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.84,0:08:03.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,D-Do you still have the ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.88,0:08:05.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Is the Golden Eye safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.94,0:08:10.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's fine. I kept my fist tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:13.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.58,0:08:17.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:19.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.20,0:08:25.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The jewel is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.74,0:08:27.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.81,0:08:31.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The jewel was removed without \Ndamaging the ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.33,0:08:32.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Look! It's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.50,0:08:36.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That white hang glider belongs to Kid, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.65,0:08:38.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.75,0:08:42.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,C-Cartier-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.77,0:08:44.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.26,0:08:49.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I thought nobody could escape\N from this floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.48,0:08:53.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It seems you've underestimated him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:56.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't know about your French cat burglar,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.94,0:09:00.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but Kid is a master thief who \Nmakes the impossible possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.60,0:09:05.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.53,0:09:09.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm going after Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.05,0:09:11.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right, we're on it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.91,0:09:13.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.04,0:09:19.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let's let that dumb investigator \Nchase after a dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:20.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That was a dummy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.80,0:09:22.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.80,0:09:27.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's a black balloon attached \Nto the hang glider from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:29.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're right. That does seem like a dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.97,0:09:31.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But then he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.82,0:09:35.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We haven't lost yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.04,0:09:36.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You see, the ring is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.56,0:09:37.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.74,0:09:42.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I found an unconscious man in \Nthe bathroom supply closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.26,0:09:44.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?! What man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.57,0:09:46.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A-Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:48.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...it looks like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.57,0:09:51.07,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-He's Cartier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:55.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.12,0:09:58.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I thought you seemed overly casual...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:10:00.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But you're Kid in disguise!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.34,0:10:02.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:07.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.60,0:10:14.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's the ruckus?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.22,0:10:18.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The inspector is scuffling with Kid \Nin the exhibit room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:19.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.69,0:10:21.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He needs our help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.22,0:10:22.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right! Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.78,0:10:28.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.99,0:10:34.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Glass with titanium alloy wires inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:38.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.58,0:10:43.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But all those wires ruined the view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.06,0:10:45.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.75,0:10:49.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can replace that elevator \Nonce this is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.18,0:10:51.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and you'll be able to see \Nthe magnificent view again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:53.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.01,0:10:59.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...these wires are on the inside \Nof this observation elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:02.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In other words, they're part of the car\N that takes passengers up and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.36,0:11:05.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And outside of the car...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.46,0:11:09.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...is just regular heavy plate glass, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.68,0:11:29.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,K-Knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.06,0:11:30.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm the real thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.05,0:11:32.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.93,0:11:35.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The sleeping Cartier-san's face...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:40.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.83,0:11:44.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...the riot cop who hauled \Nin the floodlights!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.38,0:11:49.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, everything's going \Naccording to plan, Jii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.50,0:11:52.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now I just have to wait for \Nthe inspector and company.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.70,0:11:56.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Still, they fell for it \Nhook, line, and sinker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.96,0:12:00.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I attached a dummy ornament to \Nthe underside of the ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.37,0:12:05.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...and just turned it around!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:09.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm a genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.91,0:12:20.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.65,0:12:21.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Whose?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.98,0:12:27.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:30.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bonsoir,{\i0} Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.73,0:12:36.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you're still there, then I imagine \Nyou're gloating over the stolen ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.88,0:12:39.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,C-Chat Noir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.50,0:12:49.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,F-Fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.84,0:12:55.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I would never put the \Nreal one on your finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.47,0:12:57.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then where is the real one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.18,0:13:02.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Look, the real one is on the tie pin \Nattached to Monsieur Nakamori's tie...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.61,0:13:06.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-The end's been chopped off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:11.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes. I expected that you \Nwould turn off the lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.76,0:13:17.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so I took advantage of the darkness and \Ncut off the end of the inspector's tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.08,0:13:18.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.29,0:13:24.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And that's how I got the real ring, \Nattached to the tie with the pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.18,0:13:29.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I realized the other one \Nwas a fake right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.72,0:13:35.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because I knew Cartier would never put \NMarie Antoinette's ring on the inspector's finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:41.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I went to the trouble of calling \Nyou like this to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.62,0:13:45.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I just had to get this ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.79,0:13:48.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's the last precious \Npiece of the collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.00,0:13:53.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So that's why you provoked me and \Ntempted me to come here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:59.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,After your theft, you sent the hidden, \Nremote-controlled hang glider on the roof flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.32,0:14:02.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You made it look like \NKid the Phantom Thief was escaping,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.33,0:14:06.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so you would have an excuse \Nto leave that floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.27,0:14:11.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,With no other tall buildings in the area \Nand a dim night view, it would've been
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:17.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,tough to spot Chat Noir's black paraglider\N coming out of that penthouse window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:19.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.18,0:14:24.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"Investigating insurance agent"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:27.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...Ruby Jones-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.80,0:14:32.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear. How long have you known?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.40,0:14:36.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Since I overheard you \Ntalking to that girl, Aoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.09,0:14:43.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Like me, Ruby said her name was \Nchosen from her birthstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.09,0:14:46.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And she said our birthdays are close, \Nso we should be friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.30,0:14:52.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But when we were talking about it,\N Cartier-san butted in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:57.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And he said, "Then was your \Nfriend born in December?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.01,0:15:03.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,After hearing her birthday, \Nyou said yours was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.01,0:15:08.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Certainly, in France, ruby is the birthstone \Nfor March and sapphire is April,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:13.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but in America and Japan, ruby is the July \Nbirthstone, while sapphire is September.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.94,0:15:18.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,With a two-month difference, \Nyou wouldn't say they were "close," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.24,0:15:25.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And only in France is malachite \Nthe birthstone for December.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.39,0:15:27.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The countries are slightly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.34,0:15:30.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And that's how I figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:34.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You were French pretending to be American.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.85,0:15:37.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Huh. I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.66,0:15:43.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And I know that you're a sad thief who's \Ncollecting your parent's personal effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.47,0:15:48.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Chat Noir boldly left a replica \Nof the accessory at the site
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:54.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,that looked exactly like the \NMarie accessory he stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.15,0:15:58.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The only thing different was that \Nit didn't contain the cat's-eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:01.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but looked like the jewel had \Nbeen taken out of the replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.78,0:16:06.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We don't know yet if they \Nwere really Marie's mementos,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:11.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but either way, those embedded \Ncat's-eyes are valuable jewels,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:14.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and the designs are close \Nto items from that period,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.29,0:16:18.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so even historians tend to \Nthink that they're genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.34,0:16:24.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So you left a perfect replica \Nat the scene of each crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.80,0:16:28.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,which means you had\N the replica beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.97,0:16:34.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But considering the original accessories \Nwere sealed away for 30 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.31,0:16:39.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,someone much older than you \Nmust have made the replicas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.09,0:16:46.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On top of that, if I imagine Chat Noir's\N black costume as mourning garb,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:50.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,it easily leads to this answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.45,0:16:55.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My, my. For a thief, you certainly \Nsound like a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.15,0:16:57.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.93,0:17:04.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ken Mitsuishi, a Marie Antoinette fan and \Nfather of Dan, had my jewelry designer father
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.30,0:17:08.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,create the seven accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.99,0:17:13.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He said he wanted to give his wife \Naccessories that Marie herself could have worn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.27,0:17:20.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But they turned out to be such fine works \Nof art that Ken claimed they were real.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:24.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My father committed suicide \Nrather than sully Marie's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.05,0:17:28.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And Ken Mitsuishi reluctantly \Nsealed the accessories away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.12,0:17:34.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then I found my father's last words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.02,0:17:38.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,To honor his will, I took the accessories \Nback before they appeared on the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.39,0:17:42.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is a keepsake from my father, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.63,0:17:46.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:47.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.88,0:17:51.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right. Unfortunately, \Nwhat you have there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.46,0:17:53.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,is a fake I prepared myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.94,0:17:56.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,When the inspector flipped \Nhis tie over his shoulder,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:17:59.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I made the switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.65,0:18:05.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then you knew it was a fake, but still \Nstole the ring from his finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.28,0:18:11.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes. If I didn't live up to your expectations\N by turning off the lights and appearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.70,0:18:14.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,you might have gone with \Na more reckless gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.16,0:18:26.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.13,0:18:30.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Too bad, but it looks like I'll \Njust have to give up on that ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.74,0:18:35.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you have it, I can at least take comfort \Nthat it probably won't hit the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.82,0:18:39.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No. This is a memento \Nfrom your beloved father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:43.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm going to return it to you\N in five seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.33,0:18:44.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Silly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.99,0:18:47.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Where do you think I am right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.79,0:18:51.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Even the legendary Houdini \Ncouldn't manage a feat like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.49,0:18:54.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Three... two...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.20,0:18:55.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,One.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.59,0:19:15.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it. How...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.60,0:19:20.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're on Air France flight 273,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:24.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,departing from Narita at 11:55.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.86,0:19:29.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,An educated guess based on the schedule time \Nof the crime and this hotel's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.49,0:19:32.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then you've got a confederate \Non this flight...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.74,0:19:36.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,B-But why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:39.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why would you return it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.52,0:19:41.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.47,0:19:46.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...the reason for your crimes\N resembles my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:47.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.01,0:19:52.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-There he is! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:53.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.26,0:19:55.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A hole?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.26,0:19:59.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't let him get away! Lower the elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.40,0:20:00.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:04.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-Idiot! That's just black paper\N made to look like a hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.52,0:20:11.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.64,0:20:15.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:17.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Is it okay to stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.54,0:20:25.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What the hell?! Hey! \NWe're gonna crash after all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.89,0:20:30.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All rightie...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.26,0:20:31.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're going to fly away again, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.85,0:20:36.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In that garish white suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:40.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:44.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Completely different from a cat burglar who \Ndresses in black to avoid being noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.67,0:20:49.07,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A phantom thief is audacious \Nand magnificent to behold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:03.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:09.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}merci{\i0}, Kaito Kuroba.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:12.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget you, Kaito Kuroba.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.49,0:21:20.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Paris Collection, \NParis Collection! {\i1}C'est bon!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.12,0:21:26.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A phantom thief calling \Nherself a black cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:30.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now that she's achieved her objective, \NI doubt she'll appear again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.46,0:21:34.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.65,0:21:39.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As a phantom thief, I'm an \Nextraordinary illusionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.22,0:21:44.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Whether I achieve my objective or not, \Nas long as people desire it, the show will go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.61,0:21:49.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, see you next illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.40,0:23:23.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, while Jii-chan is \Nenjoying the Paris Collection,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.80,0:23:26.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I think I'll start getting \Nready for my next heist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.29,0:23:27.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The prey is a black opal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.68,0:23:32.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But then a shady mastermind called \NNightmare proposes teaming up with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.49,0:23:35.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On top of that, Interpol and a \Nhigh school detective show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.56,0:23:38.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wait, that jerk's gonna be here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.03,0:23:40.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That leaves me without any room for error!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:43.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}: \NDark Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:43.41,Signs,,0,0,0,,Dark Knight
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.41,0:23:46.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Step right this way. Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.12,0:23:47.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't miss the illusion.
